        <title>Install SPFE Open Toolkit</title>

        <p> You may use the SPFE Open Toolkit in a Microsoft Windows or a Unix-like environment,
            including OS X or Linux. Use these guidelines to install and test the SPFE Open Toolkit and
            the third-party tools it will need.</p>

        <p> Installation involves the following tasks:</p>

        <ul>
            <li><p>installing the Java Development Kit</p></li>
            <li><p>installing Apache Ant</p></li>
            <li><p>installing the SPFE Open Toolkit</p></li>
            <li><p>configuring your environment</p></li>
            <li><p>testing the installation</p></li>
        </ul>

        <section>
            <title>Installing the Java Development Kit</title>
            
            <p> The SPFE Open Toolkit uses Java to run its build scripts. You may have the 
                Java Runtime Engine (JRE) installed, but that's not sufficient. You will need the 
                Java Development Kit (JDK), Standard Edition, installed. To install the JDK, go to 
                <link-external href="http://www.oracle.com/technetwork/java/javase/downloads/index.html">
                    oracle.com/technetwork/java/javase/downloads
                </link-external> and follow the instructions for your operating system.</p>
            
            <ul>
                <li><p>
                    <link-external href="http://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/technotes/guides/install/windows_jdk_install.html">
                    JDK installation instructions for Microsoft Windows
                    </link-external>
                </p></li>
                <li><p>
                    <link-external href="http://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/technotes/guides/install/mac_jdk.html">
                        JDK installation instructions for (Mac) OS X
                    </link-external>
                </p></li>
                <li><p>
                    <link-external href="http://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/technotes/guides/install/linux_jdk.html">
                        JDK installation instructions for Linux
                    </link-external>
                </p></li>
            </ul>

        </section>


        <section>
            <title>Installing Apache Ant</title>
            
            <p>While Java is the engine that runs the SPFE Open Toolkit build system, Apache Ant orchestrates it. Ant is a
            Java library and command-line tool that will manage the sequence of operations needed to transform a content
            set to finished output. Ant is open-source software that's freely available at 
            <link-external href="http://ant.apache.org">ant.apache.org</link-external>. Refer to the installation
            instructions at 
                <link-external href="http://ant.apache.org/manual/install.html">
                    ant.apache.org/manual/install.html
                </link-external>. To simplify the installation process for Microsoft Windows, you may use the WinAnt installer available at
                <link-external href="https://code.google.com/p/winant/">code.google.com/p/winant</link-external>.</p>       
        </section>

